other_tests.findings: Patient was hypoglycemic at 39 mg/dL with insulin of 40 mcU/mL at 26 hours into the fast and a proinsulin of 35 pmol/L.
Showed a step-up of venous insulin levels at injection of the superior mesenteric artery and proximal and mid-splenic artery.
Showed focal uptake in the neck of the pancreas with an SUV of 12.
Revealed four subcentimeter neuroendocrine tumors that were positive for insulin, consistent with a diagnosis of multiple microadenomas.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Post-surgery, the patient had normalization of biochemical levels and resolution of her symptoms.
